1. insert bibtex entry depending on the type of document (inproceedings,
article or book) knowing that each type of document have a different
set of information fields represented in the examples above,

2. search for references by year or author or title knowing that in authors
field there is a list of authors;

3. allow some advanced searches that return the ”AND” result between
two fields Author and Year;

4. given a key, print on the screen the associated bibliographic reference
in text format;

5. given a set of keys produce a file with all corresponding bibliographic
references in bibtex format and a txt file with all those references in
text format;

6. generate the dot file representing semantic relations (based on common
keywords in annote field) between references.
